  "notes": "Live Admin GraphQL 2026-04 evidence for metaobjectDefinitionUpdate immutability. The executable parity targets prove a standard definition enabled from Shopify's template catalog returns one IMMUTABLE userError and remains unchanged on immediate read-after-reject. The same live fixture records that this shop cannot create arbitrary non-standard `shopify--*` definitions (`NOT_AUTHORIZED`) and that changing `displayNameKey` on a definition linked to product options returns Shopify's IMMUTABLE display-name error. Focused runtime tests cover deterministic local standard-template metadata, checked-in standard-template types without metadata, and reserved `shopify--` namespace staging because the local model can represent those cases. The local model does not yet represent Shopify's linked-product-options or app-config-managed definition flags, so endpoint docs state that limitation rather than fabricating parity targets."
